      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/1106" title="Spring BlazeDS Integration Test Drive: Updated for M2">Spring BlazeDS Integration Test Drive: Updated for M2</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by jeremyg484 on Thu, 2009-03-12 09:36        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_6 first last active"><a href="/presentations" rel="tag" title="A link to a technical article about Spring" class="active">Technical Article</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>
Christophe Coenraets, Senior Technical Evangelist for Adobe, has updated his excellent set of samples to get you up and running quickly with Spring BlazeDS Integration M2.  See <a href="http://coenraets.org/blog/2009/03/springblazeds-integration-test-drive-m2-update-available/">his blog</a> for a link to the download and installation instructions.
</p>
<p>
&quot;To help developers get started with the integration, I put together a new “Spring / BlazeDS Test Drive”.  This Test Drive consists of a minimal version of Tomcat with BlazeDS and the “Spring / BlazeDS integration” preconfigured and ready to use. It also includes a series of samples running “out-of-the-box” that should allow you to get up and running integrating Flex (and Adobe AIR) with Spring in a matter of minutes.&quot;
</p>
  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
</div></div> <!-- /node-inner, /node -->
<div id="node-972" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/972" title="New Spring BlazeDS Integration Test Drive">New Spring BlazeDS Integration Test Drive</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by jeremyg484 on Tue, 2009-01-27 16:14        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_6 first last active"><a href="/presentations" rel="tag" title="A link to a technical article about Spring" class="active">Technical Article</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>Christophe Coenraets, Senior Technical Evangelist for Adobe, has assembled a great new set of samples to get you up and running quickly with Spring BlazeDS Integration M1.  See <a href="http://coenraets.org/blog/2009/01/new-springblazeds-integration-test-drive/">his blog</a> for a link to the download and installation instructions.</p>
<p>&quot;To help developers get started with the integration, I put together a new “Spring / BlazeDS Test Drive”.  This Test Drive consists of a minimal version of Tomcat with BlazeDS and the “Spring / BlazeDS integration” preconfigured and ready to use. It also includes a series of samples running “out-of-the-box” that should allow you to get up and running integrating Flex (and Adobe AIR) with Spring in a matter of minutes.&quot; </p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
